news.title: Google says it will invest around $6.4 billion in cloud infrastructure in Germany
news.content: BERLIN (Reuters) -Alphabet'​s Google said ‌on Tuesday that it ‌will invest 5.5 billion euros ($6.41 billion) ⁠in ‌Germany in the coming years in ‍a push to expand its infrastructure and data ​centre capacity in ‌Europe's largest economy.  The plans include a new data centre in Dietzenbach, close ⁠to Frankfurt,​ Google ​said, according to information it provided ‍ahead ⁠of a press conference in Berlin.
